node.text:
I’m so pleased to be part of the #sharethemicfoodandbev campaign, and, indeed, to be sharing the mic with the fabulous @zoeadjonyoh, chef, author and activist and author of Zoe’s Ghana Kitchen. What ‘sharing the mic’ means here is that Zoe will be taking over my Instagram account for 24 hours from 12 midday tomorrow, Monday the 20th, to 12 midday on Tuesday July 21st. You are in for a treat! 
This is a campaign dedicated to amplifying the voices of Black women whose contributions to the food culture have been customarily overlooked, and it’s a real honour to #keepsharingthemic

node.text:
I’ve made a video-selfie with details of how to make my Emergency Brownies for #hopefromhome on #worldhealthday in support of health workers and medical teams. I know that many of you who would like to donate are just not able to right now, but if you can please do, by going to hopefromhome.tiltify.com.
.
#recipeoftheday

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Nigella on August 24, 2021 tagging @helencathcart, and @palomarsoho. May be an image of tomato.

node.text:
This week’s Guest Recipe from the #CookbookCorner archive is this fabulous tomato salad from the #PalomarCookbook @palomarsoho 
.

And to get the recipe, either go to nigella.com or click on link in bio. What I mean by this, is that you tap on my name, which will take you to a page that has a link on it that says www.nigella.com/instagram. When you click on this link, it will take you to a page of photographs: click on the photograph you want the recipe of, and you will be taken to it!
.
Photograph by @helencathcart

node.text:
And #RecipeOfTheDay is Quick Calamari with Garlic Mayonnaise! I always have some squid stashed in the freezer so I can make this on a whim!
.

And to get the recipe, either go to nigella.com or click on link in bio. What I mean by this, is that you tap on my name, which will take you to a page that has a link on it that says www.nigella.com/instagram. When you click on this link, it will take you to a page of photographs: click on the photograph you want the recipe of, and you will be taken to it! 
.
Photograph by Lis Parsons

node.text:
🇩🇪📖 Ich freue mich so sehr, dass mein neues Buch, „Kochen, essen, leben“ heute am 24. August bei DK Verlag (@dkverlag) erscheint! Es nimmt einen ganz besonderen Platz in meinem Herzen ein, dieses Buch, das mich genaehrt hat, mich begleitet hat und mir eine Zuflucht ins Glück während des Lockdowns gegeben hat. Es ist auf keinen Fall ein Covid-Kochbuch, sondern eine Reflektion auf das, was Kochen bedeutet, eine Feier meiner Lieblingszutaten, des unendlichen Genusses, den ich vom Essen bekomme und eine Sammlung der Rezepte, die ich immer und immer wieder koche, für mich alleine oder für einen ganzen Tisch voller Freunde. Dieses Buch ist dafuer gedacht, jeden Tag koestlich zu machen. 

Link in Story!
#cookbookcorner

#RecipeOfTheDay is a gorgeous one: Green Pasta with Blue Cheese! It’s new to nigella.com (from the pages of #nigellissima) and I’m very pleased to have it on the site. Of course, you don’t need to use green pasta, but this is how I make it. And I should add that while I make this for 2, the amounts would actually feed 3 not too shabbily!
.

And to get the recipe, either go to nigella.com or click on link in bio. What I mean by this, is that you tap on my name, which will take you to a page that has a link on it that says www.nigella.com/instagram. When you click on this link, it will take you to a page of photographs: click on the photograph you want the recipe of, and you will be taken to it! 
.
Photograph by @petrinatinslay
